</div>
<br>
<br>
<div class="view">
  <%= f.label :title %> of story<br>
  <%= f.text_area :title %>
</div>
<br>
<br>

Title Tips:<br><br>
A title can entice a reader to take a closer look at a story.<br><br>
A title should be interesting, convey the tone or central idea of the story, and be easy to remember.<br><br>
A title can include a word or phrase that runs through the story or has a hidden meaning revealed in the story.<br><br>
A title can include the name of a character or place important to the plot.<br><br>
A title can be a play on words or a popular expression related to the story's subject.<br><br>
A title is commonly three words long, but can be one word.<br><br>
Titles with more than six words are uncommon.<br><br>

<br><br>

<div class="field">
  <%= f.label :description %> of story<br>
  <%= f.text_area :description %><br>
</div>

<br><br>

Description Tips:<br><br>

Give a short summary of the contents and plot.<br><br>
Ask unanswered questions without giving away the story ("Will Mary find out who the mysterious visitor is?").<br><br>
Be persuasive and encourage interest.<br><br>
Discuss or quote the main character.<br><br>
Describe the setting.<br><br>


